article.headline: Idaho St. 76, UC Davis 49
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho (AP) -- Senior guard David Schroeder scored 21 points and added 11 rebounds, as Idaho State rode a tenacious defense to a 76-49 rout of UC Davis Saturday night. The game was tight early on, as both teams struggled to find an offensive rhythm. Schroeder hit a three-pointer with 10:18 left in the first half to tie the score at 10-10 and spark a 10-0 Idaho State run as they grabbed a 17-10 advantage. Idaho State (4-5) held UC Davis to just three field goals the rest of the half and opened up a 30-17 halftime lead. UC Davis shot 28 percent from the field in the first half, including going 2-15 from three-point range. A 14-6 run by UC Davis early in the second half cut the ISU lead to eight points, at 41-33, as the Aggies tried to claw their way back into the game. Idaho State responded by scoring the next 10 points to push the lead to 18. The Bengals continued to pull away and when Austin Kilpatrick drained a three-pointer with 4:16 left in the game, ISU found themselves up 69-40 and well on their way to a comfortable victory. Ari Warmerdam led UC Davis with 12 points, and Jesse Lopez Low added 11 points and 8 rebounds. Vince Oliver, the team's leading scorer, was shut out, going 0-9 from the field. Akbar Abdul-Ahad had 13 points and dished out 11 assists for Idaho State.
